  "riddle": "1. Seek out a land surrounded by sapphire waves, home to fewer souls than many a bustling hamlet. How many call Dongji Island their home?\n\n2. Journey to the realm touching the Bay of Bengal, where myriad cultures meld. What is the population noted within its borders?\n\n3. Should you delve into the governance of the nation shaped by the letter \"V,\" you’ll uncover a linguistic tapestry. How many languages can you find woven through its discourse?\n\n4. What peaks rise beneath the documentary of governance for this Southeast Asian nation? Discover its elevation.\n\n5. A place of worship often stands sentinel in cities. Count how many churches can be found nearby this center of politics.\n\n6. Now, combine your newfound figures from clues 4 and 5. What is their absolute difference?\n\n7. For an intriguing transformation, consider the previous clue's outcome. How many different divisors exist for that number?\n\n8. Hidden wisdom lies in the philosophies of a prominent leader. Search for a page dedicated to these insights. How many languages reflect their teachings?\n\n9. Travel to the land down under; what is Australia’s current population?\n\n10. A kingdom once ruled over the fertile grounds of Sumatra. When did the majestic Pagaruyung kingdom's reign begin and end? Identify those significant years.\n\n11. A writing system serves to bridge tongues and ideas. What numeral rests beside the title of the script used for Javanese languages?\n\n12. An islet off the coast of Cebu greets you next. What region of the Philippines embraces Pescador Island?\n\n13. Ascend to the heights that crown this Filipino gem. How high does Pescador Island rise above sea level?\n\n14. Travelers often leave behind trails in the form of ratings. What score do they award Pescador Island?\n\n15. Collate the elevation you discovered in clue 13 with the visitor's score from clue 14. What numeral emerges from their sum?\n\n16. In the name of the island explored, how many vowels pain